The ANC has called a special national executive committee (NEC) meeting, which is expected to discuss among other things, the future of President Jacob Zuma. The meeting will take place at St. Georges Hotel in Centurion on Monday after it was cancelled last week. Mondayâ€™s meeting comes after ANC President Cyril Ramaphosa met other members of the top six leadership where he gave a briefing on the progress of his negotiations with Zuma on the call for him to resign from the presidency. ANC spokesperson Pule Mabe has confirmed the meeting but said he was not at liberty to speak on its agenda. -TNA Reporter